    <p><strong>Key differences between Indian and imported convection ovens:</strong> Indian-made ovens are significantly cheaper but typically have thinner insulation, shorter lifespans, and less precise temperature control. Imported brands like <a href="/blog/sinmag-oven-review">Sinmag</a> offer better build quality, more consistent temperatures (variance of ±3°C vs ±8–10°C for many Indian brands), and longer warranties. Premium European brands (Unox, Rational) bring digital controls, programmable recipes, and exceptional build quality — but at 2–3x the price.</p>

