        <div class="faq-a">Gas ovens cost 10–20% more upfront but are significantly cheaper to operate in India. A gas oven typically costs ₹300–₹600/day in fuel, while an equivalent electric oven may cost ₹500–₹1,200/day depending on your electricity rates. Over 5 years, a gas oven can save ₹2–5 lakh in operating costs. However, electric ovens are easier to install and offer more precise temperature control. Read our detailed <a href="/blog/gas-vs-electric-oven-bakery">gas vs electric oven comparison</a> for the full analysis.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which are the best bakery oven brands available in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The best oven brands available in India by segment: <strong>Budget</strong> — Genius, Ekon, Cookman (Indian). <strong>Mid-range (best value)</strong> — Sinmag (Taiwan), Berjaya (Malaysia). <strong>Premium</strong> — Salva (Spain), Bongard (France), WP Bakery (Germany) for bakery ovens; Rational (Germany) and Unox (Italy) for combi ovens. For most Indian bakeries, Sinmag offers the best quality-to-price ratio. See our full <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-brands-india">bakery equipment brands India</a> guide.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I get a loan or EMI for buying a bakery oven in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. You can finance a bakery oven through: (1) Supplier EMI plans — 12–36 months, 20–30% down payment; (2) MSME loans from banks — 9–14% interest, up to 5-year tenure; (3) Mudra loans (PMMY) — up to ₹10 lakh with no collateral; (4) Equipment leasing — monthly rental instead of purchase. Most options require basic KYC, business registration, and 6+ months of business banking history. Read our complete <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-financing">equipment financing</a> guide.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the price of a commercial pizza oven in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Commercial pizza oven prices in India range from ₹40,000 for a basic 2-pizza electric model to ₹10 lakh for a premium Italian wood-fired oven. Electric pizza ovens: ₹40,000–₹5,00,000. Gas pizza ovens: ₹60,000–₹4,50,000. Wood-fired pizza ovens: ₹25,000–₹10,00,000. The most popular choice for Indian pizzerias is a double-deck electric pizza oven at ₹90,000–₹1,80,000.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How much does it cost to set up a complete bakery with ovens in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A complete bakery setup in India costs ₹3–5 lakh for a small neighbourhood bakery, ₹8–15 lakh for a medium commercial bakery, and ₹20–50 lakh for a large production bakery. Ovens typically account for 30–50% of total equipment cost. Other major costs include mixers, proofers, display counters, refrigeration, and kitchen infrastructure. See our detailed <a href="/blog/bakery-setup-cost-india">bakery setup cost</a> breakdown.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Are prices listed here inclusive of GST? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">No. All prices listed in this guide are ex-showroom, excluding 18% GST. For example, an oven listed at ₹1,00,000 will cost ₹1,18,000 with GST. Installation charges (₹5,000–₹50,000) and delivery charges are also typically extra. Always confirm the total landed price including GST, delivery, and installation before making a purchase decision.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

